steps.instruction:
1. Preheat the oven to 350F
2. Line a standard muffin pan with paper or silicon muffin cups and grease the cups
3. In a large mixing bowl, whisk together the cocoa, flour, sugar, baking powder, espresso powder, baking soda, salt and chocolate chips
4. Set that aside
5. In a medium sized mixing bowl, whisk together the eggs, milk, vanilla, and vinegar 
6. Add the wet ingredients, along with the melted butter
7. Stir to blend
8. Coop the batter into the prepares muffin pan 
9. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes
10. Remove from the oven and allow to cool for 5 minutes to remove them from the pan
11. Set them on a rack and allow them to cool for about 15 minutes
